cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the problem of scene classification from optical remote sensing images using supervised metric learning strategies. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a hierarchical approach to organizing the classes based on their visual similarities, which involves clustering (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Finally, the paper deals with remote sensing data, which falls under the domain of graphics (cs.GR).
